from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV

grid = {'n_neighbors': np.arange(1, 31, step = 2, dtype='int'),
        'metric' : ('euclidean', 'manhattan', 'chebyshev')
       }

model = KNeighborsClassifier()

gs = GridSearchCV(model, param_grid=grid, scoring='f1', cv = 5, n_jobs=-1)

gs.fit(X_train, y_train)

Learning Curves¶

In [13]:
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import learning_curve

model = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=19, metric='manhattan')

train_sizes, train_scores, test_scores, fit_times, _ = learning_curve(model, X_train, y_train,
                                                         train_sizes=np.linspace(0.1, 1.0, 10), cv=5,
                                                         n_jobs=-1, scoring='f1', return_times=True)

train_scores_mean = np.mean(train_scores, axis=1)
train_scores_std = np.std(train_scores, axis=1)

test_scores_mean = np.mean(test_scores, axis=1)
test_scores_std = np.std(test_scores, axis=1)

fit_times_mean = np.mean(fit_times, axis=1)
fit_times_std = np.std(fit_times, axis=1)
In [14]:
plt.figure(figsize=(14,8))
plt.title('KNN Learning curve f1 score by size')

sns.lineplot(x=train_sizes, y=train_scores_mean, marker='o')
plt.fill_between(train_sizes,train_scores_mean + train_scores_std,
                 train_scores_mean - train_scores_std, alpha = 0.1, color="b")

sns.lineplot(x=train_sizes, y=test_scores_mean, marker='o')
plt.fill_between(train_sizes, test_scores_mean + test_scores_std,
                 test_scores_mean - test_scores_std, alpha = 0.1, color='orange')

plt.legend(['Train f1 score', 'CV f1 score'])
plt.xlabel('train sizes')
plt.ylabel('f1 score')
plt.show()

from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV

grid = {'C' : np.linspace(0.1, 1, 10),
        'penalty': ('l1', 'l2')
       }

model = LogisticRegression(class_weight='balanced', solver='saga', max_iter=500)

gs = GridSearchCV(model, param_grid=grid, scoring='f1', cv=5, n_jobs=-1)

gs.fit(X_train, y_train)

from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.model_selection import learning_curve

model = LogisticRegression(penalty='l2', C = 3.0,
                           class_weight='balanced', solver='saga', max_iter=500)

train_sizes, train_scores, test_scores, fit_times, _ = learning_curve(model, X_train, y_train,
                                                         train_sizes=np.linspace(0.1, 1.0, 10), cv=5,
                                                         n_jobs=-1, scoring='f1', return_times=True)

train_scores_mean = np.mean(train_scores, axis=1)

test_scores_std = np.std(test_scores, axis=1)

fit_times_std = np.std(fit_times, axis=1)

       }

gs.fit(X_train, y_train)
